---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Header from "@/components/Header.astro";
import Footer from "@/components/Footer.astro";
import Breadcrumb from "@/components/Breadcrumb.astro";
import { linkWithBase } from "@/utils/linkWithBase";
import { SITE } from "@/config";
---

<Layout
	title={`About | ${SITE.title}`}
	description="About Kyle Skrinak"
>
	<Header />
	<Breadcrumb />
	<main id="main-content" class="app-layout pb-12">
		<h1 class="text-2xl font-semibold sm:text-3xl">About</h1>

		<section class="app-prose mt-8">
			<h2>Thanks for stopping by</h2>

			<p>
				Hello and thanks for stopping by. I <a href={linkWithBase("/blog/2016-10-31-first-blog-post/")}>started this blog in 2016</a> as an exercise in using <a href="https://jekyllrb.com/">Jekyll</a>, a static website generator with the <a href="https://mmistakes.github.io/minimal-mistakes/">Minimal Mistakes</a> theme. I discovered I could create a feature-rich web blog serving only HTML resourcesâ€”no server-side runtime required.
			</p>

			<p>
				In January 2026, I migrated the blog from Jekyll to <a href="https://astro.build/">Astro</a>, a modern static site generator built on <a href="https://nodejs.org/">Node.js</a> and <a href="https://www.npmjs.com/">npm</a>. The site now uses the <a href="https://github.com/satnaing/astro-paper">AstroPaper</a> theme as a foundation. This migration gave me the chance to modernize the blog's tooling while preserving all the content and history.
			</p>

			<p>
				In 2022, I transitioned away from the Drupal ecosystem after years of working deeply with the platform. While I still respect Drupal and its community, I've been exploring a broader range of technologies and approaches ever since.
			</p>

			<p>
				By day, I manage web development and system administration. My interests span cloud infrastructure (AWS, Azure), content management systems, and modern web frameworks. I'm also a fan of low-carb eating, which shows up regularly on this blog. I write in Markdown and NeoVim because I enjoy the simplicity and focus they provide.
			</p>

			<p>
				Currently, I am the Senior Manager of the Digital Experience Platform Team for <a href="https://www.gilead.com/">Gilead Sciences</a>. Our team is responsible for the reliable hosting and management of Gilead's websites, supporting systems like Sitecore, Azure, and AWS.
			</p>

			<h2>Technologies & Topics</h2>
			<ul>
				<li>Web development and static site generators (Astro, Jekyll, Drupal)</li>
				<li>Package management and build tools (NPM, Node.js)</li>
				<li>Digital experience platforms and content management systems (Sitecore, Drupal)</li>
				<li>Cloud infrastructure and DevOps (AWS, Azure)</li>
				<li>Open source technologies and communities</li>
				<li>Low-carb lifestyle and personal wellness</li>
				<li>Technical writing and documentation</li>
			</ul>

			<h2>Low-Carb Living</h2>
			<p>
				Since June 2017, I've followed a low-carb diet under the guidance of Dr. Eric Westman at Duke University. It's transformed my health and helped me maintain sustainable weight loss. I write about this journey regularly on the blog. For my full story, resources, and recommendations, read <a href={linkWithBase("/lchf")}>my low-carb living page</a>.
			</p>

			<h2>Get in Touch</h2>
			<p>
				You can find me on <a href="https://github.com/kyleskrinak">GitHub</a>, <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/kyleskrinak/">LinkedIn</a>, or <a href="https://x.com/screenack">X</a>.
			</p>
		</section>
	</main>
	<Footer />
</Layout>
